rComments: John Coleman was my professor for a first-year seminar, and he was great! Really cares for his students and provided us with tools for success in the class. Such a nice guy - make sure he is your prof !!

Excellent lecturer. You can tell he loves what he does, and he is very accommodating to his students by lecturing at a good, understandable pace. He also repeats phrases, which is great for taking notes. BEST LECTURER EVER!!!!!!! Your the best Coleman!

He's a great lecturer. He explains his goals really clearly and goes at a good pace so that everyone is able to absorb what he's teaching. Plus the questions for the midterm is relevant to what he hinted during the lectures as well as the recommended readings.

He explains concepts clearly with use of examples, his test are fair(10 of the questions were exactly the ones he had put in his lecture slides.). He sticks to the textbook and readings are manageable. The best thing about him is his slow-paced lectures so you can understand everything and have enough time to take notes!
